OL,3,CInquest investigates if factory worker
OL,4,Cwho died was exposed to toxic gas
OL,6,FManaging Director of Futamura Adrian
OL,7,FCave told the court that he agreed
OL,8,Fwith the HSE that H2S must have made
OL,9,Fits way into the pump house via the
OL,10,Fdrainage system by the time the fire
OL,11,Fservice took its measurements.
OL,13,FHowever, he reiterated that there is
OL,14,Fno evidence to prove that it was
OL,15,Fpresent when Mr Cole was found.
OL,17,FHe also said that because the entire
OL,18,FFutamura plant has a sulphurous smell,
OL,19,Fit is difficult to accept the
OL,20,Feyewitness memories of the rotten egg
OL,21,Fsmell as proof of the presence of H2S.
